
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dpkg-parsechangelog` baraye khandan va tajziyeh file changelog (tarikhche taghirat) az package Debian estefade mishavad.  In dastoor etela'at ra az file changelog kharej mikonad va an ra be shekle motafavet namayesh midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-l`   --> 📜 Namayesh kol file changelog.
    🔹 `-S`   --> 👀 Namayesh source package name.
    🔹 `-vVER` --> 🏷️ Namayesh etela'at version khass. (VER = version number)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dpkg-parsechangelog

    🔹 Namayesh akharin version az changelog.

    $ dpkg-parsechangelog -l

    🔹 Namayesh tamame content file changelog.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dpkg-parsechangelog -S

    🔹 Faghat name source package ra az file changelog chap mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dpkg-parsechangelog` command is used to read and parse the changelog file of a Debian package. It extracts information from the changelog file and displays it in various formats.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-l`   --> 📜 Display the entire changelog file.
    🔹 `-S`   --> 👀 Display the source package name.
    🔹 `-vVER` --> 🏷️ Display information for a specific version. (VER = version number)

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dpkg-parsechangelog

    🔹 Displays the latest version from the changelog.

    $ dpkg-parsechangelog -l

    🔹 Displays the entire content of the changelog file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dpkg-parsechangelog -S

    🔹 Prints only the source package name from the changelog file.

